#Text=JM :
#Text=I ca n't say based upon my practice ;
#Text=I keep a very small talking practice , because of my other work .

#Text=Based on my own personal engagement with the outside world , I think people are very frustrated , annoyed , mistrustful , and non-believing of anything government says , but not to the point of doing anything about it .
#Text=DS : What do you mean when you say ' doing anything about it ' ?
#Text=JM : Being activists about it .
#Text=I do n't know if it 's learned helplessness or what .
#Text=There 's apathy .
#Text=One of the most energized moments I experienced in years was when there were the large protests of marchers down the east side to the U.N. I long for the play Hair to come back .
#Text=It 's 40 years old now .
#Text=I do n't understand why it 's not back on Broadway .
#Text=DS : We have been in this war for four years .
#Text=Is it important to discuss it ?
#Text=JM : I think a lot of us lead more and more isolated existences in the midst of millions of people .
#Text=We 're on our cell phone .
#Text=We 're on our Blackberry .
#Text=We 're on our computer .
#Text=It 's all disjointed in some kind of a way .
#Text=DS : Do you think people are putting their heads in the sand , or do you think it is too much for people to process what is happening ?
#Text=JM : I think people feel impotent .
#Text=Look , people came out and did this massive election , turned over Congress , the House , the Senate , and nothing has changed .
#Text=I think people are feeling that if the vote is the thing is going to change society , and it 's not even doing that ...
#Text=Or you have to be a multi-millionaire to run for the office .
#Text=With a clean record -- who has that ?
#Text=The jury system , and mistrust of that of whether it is bought off , who gets justice and who does n't get justice .
#Text=DS : But we respond to it .
#Text=JM : Until the Mets lose a game , and then we are on to that .
#Text=We are trained to have very short attention spans .
#Text=We have become isolated and disjointed from one another , except when we have to mix .
#Text=DS : How do you think that affects personality development , that our interactions today are so two-dimensional ?
#Text=JM : It affects a lot of things .
#Text=Relationships , how we get along with each other .
#Text=You look at something like 9/11 or a disaster , and how that galvanizes and brings people together and how short-lived that is .
#Text=Then it goes back down again .
#Text=It 's as if we constantly need a jolt of that magnitude to shake us out of our complacency in the ways we live and interact .
#Text=I think it 's sad , and it 's a concern .
